        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 10:55AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1054 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles south of Fort Stockton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sierra Madera.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
